uestion. The government is encouraging local authorities to apply for the Town and Village Renewal Scheme by actively fostering collaboration at the local level. Local authorities are supported through Town Regeneration Officers—funded by the Department—who work closely with community groups, retailers, and other members of the Town Teams to help devise and deliver projects that meet local needs and priorities. This collaborative process, combined with a range of available funding streams (as illustrated by the 2023 TVRS funding of €15 million), is designed to empower local authorities and communities to create vibrant and sustainable town centres. Such efforts align with our broader mission of promoting rural and community development across Ireland.", :cosine-similarity 0.7681278570132254, :bleu-faithfulness 3.2158637016786745E-5, :rouge-l-f1 0.2156862716032296}]
